  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can Google help me track my lost Android phone by the IMEI number?",
  "response": "Google cannot directly help you track a lost Android phone using its IMEI (International Mobile Equipment Identity) number. However, there are other ways you can try to locate or secure your lost Android device:\n\n### **1. Use Google's Find My Device**  \nThis is the primary tool provided by Google to locate a lost Android phone. It requires the device to be:  \n- Turned on and connected to the internet (Wi-Fi or mobile data).  \n- Signed in to a Google account.  \n\n**Steps to use Find My Device:**  \n1. Visit [Find My Device](https://www.google.com/android/find) or use the Find My Device app on another Android device.  \n2. Sign in with the Google account linked to the lost phone.  \n3. The service will show the phone's location on a map.  \n4. You can also play a sound, lock the device, or erase its data remotely.  \n\n### **2. Contact Your Mobile Carrier**  \nWhile Google cannot track your phone using the IMEI number, your mobile carrier might be able to assist.  \n- Report the lost phone to your carrier.  \n- Provide them with the IMEI number to blacklist the device, preventing it from being used on their network.  \n- Note: Carriers generally cannot track the phone's location using the IMEI, but they can help prevent misuse.  \n\n### **3. Report to Local Authorities**  \nIf you believe your phone was stolen, report it to the local police. Provide them with the IMEI number and any other relevant details.  \n\n### **4. Check Third-Party Apps**  \nIf you had third-party tracking apps installed (e.g., Cerberus, Prey), you might be able to use them to locate the phone.  \n\n### **5. Use IMEI Tracking Websites**  \nSome websites claim to track phones using the IMEI number, but be cautious:  \n- Many of these services are scams or ineffective.  \n- Google and legitimate authorities do not support IMEI-based tracking for security reasons.  \n\n### **Prevent Future Loss**  \n- Always enable Find My Device on your Android phone.  \n- Keep your phone's location services and internet connection active.  \n- Note down your IMEI number and keep it in a safe place for emergencies.  \n\nIn summary, while Google cannot track your phone using the IMEI number, **Find My Device** is the most effective tool to locate or secure your lost Android phone.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
